e.
Other geoprocessing services ISO's andOGC's general taxonomies mentiona large number of useful geoprocessingservices, most of which currently exist only as internal software functions rather thanaddressable services: spectral classification, feature generalization,etc.
It is expected that most of these will share a "commontrunk" of metadata and interface / behavior, tobe definedinthe general service model.
